@NODE about "About Fastbar"

@{B}@{U}Distribution.. @{UU}@{UB}

This program is free-ware for those, who use a REAL Amiga,
and (presummed) paid for it.
Those who emulate the Amiga enoviroment, and like to use
Fastbar have to pay some share-ware fee.

@{B}@{U}What is it.. @{UU}@{UB}

Fastbar, is just another Screen-manager for AmigaOS, but fast!
Fastbar doesn't use the systems list of public screens.

THIS PROGRAM IS BETA!
I AM NOT RESPONSABLE FOR ANYTHING THIS PROGRAM MIGHT DO TO YOUR
SYSTEM OR LIFE OR ANYTHING ELSE ... 

@ENDNODE about
@NODE features "Main features of Fastbar"

- Fast and optional low CPU using. 
- Configureable via tooltype. 
- Fast scaling.
- Nice optional animation.
- Digital optional disk-drive/memory-usage led.
- Save WBMODE (Show only on WB.)
- Popup info windows.(wait above a item with mouse)
- Nice Arexx using system navigator. (OUDAR.exe needed in PATH)
  (Opens up drawers on your workbench, from device lister!)
@ENDNODE features
@NODE install "Install Fastbar"

@{B}@{U}To install Fastbar.. @{UU}@{UB}

Download the latest OUDAR from aminet, and copy it to c:.
Copy fastbar with its icon anywhere you want.
To make Fastbar autostart, copy it with icon to wbstartup!

@ENDNODE about
@NODE usage "How to use?"

@{B}@{U}Starting fastbar @{UU}@{UB}

Fastbar can be started from cli or from wb,
the start argument 'quiet' can be given to,
skip the welkom requester.

@{B}@{U}Configuring Startbar @{UU}@{UB}

Fastbar can be configured with the icon's
tooltypes, known options are:

WBMODE		-	1/0 (Only showup in workbench screen)
HIDE		-	1/0 (Hide always, show when pointer reaches down)
ANIMATE		-	1/0 (Animate when disappear/appear)
SMOOTH		-	VAL (Value 1/8 are valid, where 1=smoothest)
PRI		-	VAL (-127-127 setup taskpriority of Fastbar)
LEDCHECK	-	VAL (MEMORY/DISKDRIVE led's job to check)
LEDEXECUTE	-	VAL (PROGRAM, to execute for the led button)

@ENDNODE usage
